{"questionId":"11828","questionHtml":"<p>With the initial conditions as given in part (j), determine if the equilibrium point is stable or unstable.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>As&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{e^{ - t}} \\to 0\\,\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">→</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n</math></span> as&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t \\to \\infty \">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">→</mo>\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;the equilibrium point is stable. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11828","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.3k","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"With the initial conditions as given in part (j), determine if the equilibrium point is stable or unstable.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"k","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.17—Phase portrait"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}